 68k IP's. So- Maxing INT for an MA is wasted IP's as far as I'm concerned. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#FFFFCC><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub83.ezboard.com/ugraav.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Graav</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Ninja Wanna-Be</span><br>  Posts: 4<br> <font color=#660000>(9/1/02 5:39:05 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub83.ezboard.com/fthepunchingbag74708frm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2117.topic&index=9>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: agree</span><hr size=1> &quot;well,personally,I can't see Maxing INT as that important. After reading all the posts here I decided maybe I was missing something so I dumped 160K IP;s into Intelligence -increasing it to 534. I had copied all my stats down before hand and then compared them to the new 534 INT increase. I then looked at each skill that was affected by raising INT and by how many points each was raised. Then I Reset the INT back to where it was originally and increased each attribute/skill by the same number of points and did it all for 92K IP's thus saving myself 68k IP's. So- Maxing INT for an MA is wasted IP's as far as I'm concerned.&quot;<br>
<br>
The point being made here is that you can use skills EARLIER by maxing INT.  You saved yourself IPs, yes, but if you were to max INT along the way, you would get to use some nanos sooner than by not maxing INT.  I don't max INT myself, but I do see the advantages of doing it.<br>
